The antibacterial activity of the investigated essential oil was tested against four bacteria strains. The following microorganisms were used in this work: two gram-positive (
 Bacillus subtilis ATCC 6633; 
 Staphylococcus aureus ATCC 6538) and two gram-negative (
 Pseudomonas aeruginosa ATCC 27853; 
 Escherichia coli ATCC 25922) bacteria. All strains were cultured at 37 Â°C on Mueller-Hinton medium.
